source: crates/carta/tests/golden_e2e.rs
expression: output
---
An internal link to \url{start} and one to a
\href{/some/namespace/page}{page} target.

A named internal link to \href{start}{the start page} guides the reader.

External links such as \href{https://example.com}{Example} and the bare
form \url{https://example.org} both work, as does an email like
\href{mailto:user@example.com}{\nolinkurl{user@example.com}}.

An interwiki shortcut points at
\href{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki}{Wiki} for background reading.
